{"type":"message","id":"204279b8","parentId":"8b608823","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:45:57.495Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Lets create a new linkedin post in which we explain how the idea of Benchmarking AI Agents correlates with Test Driver Development in traditional software development.\nActually to start AI Agent development from creation of the Benchmark and Verifiable reward that Agent should achieve is a best way to develop a truly self evolving AI Agent","timestamp":1783356356000}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9d3c54a","parentId":"204279b8","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:46:03.780Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_257218089b8c4abfa0391ffd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2ee593656718428983d6d139","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783356357506,"responseId":"xttLaoHMFb7i7bQP96yquAE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"503ac73d","parentId":"f9d3c54a","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:46:03.994Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_257218089b8c4abfa0391ffd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783356363992}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ddfeb53","parentId":"503ac73d","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:46:03.999Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2ee593656718428983d6d139","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Content Strategy — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Business Goal\n\nGrow personal brand with focus on AI Autonomous Organizations and AI Agents. Position as a multi-company operator building at the intersection of AI and business transformation.\n\n## Posting Cadence\n\n- **Frequency:** 2-3 times per day\n- **Preferred schedule:** Every day\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n*(Carried from brand voice profile)*\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Key Messages\n\n*(The beliefs and positions every post should reinforce)*\n1. AI can be affordable and accessible — even for small businesses\n2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n3. Every company will become AI-first — the question is when, not if\n\n## Target Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who you are writing for — each post should speak to at least one)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) — Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency — Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB — Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Topics to Avoid\n\n(none — open to all topics)\n\n## Upcoming Campaigns\n\n- **Benchgen.com launch** — Benchmarking product (mention organically, not primary focus)\n- **UBOS.tech improvements** — AI Agent Orchestration Platform (mention organically, not primary focus)\n\n## Strategic Positioning\n\nPersonal brand > individual company promotion. Building reputation as an AI thought leader and multi-company operator. Content should position Andrii as the voice on AI Autonomous Organizations, not just a founder pushing products.\n\n## Pillar Balance Target\n\nWith 2-3 posts/day, aim for roughly equal coverage across all 3 pillars each week. Mix formats: thought leadership, tactical insights, personal stories, news reactions. Prioritize AI Agents and Autonomous Organizations angles across all pillars.\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Strategy created\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783356363996}}
{"type":"message","id":"721040d8","parentId":"0ddfeb53","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:46:16.679Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me draft this. Great concept — the TDD parallel is sharp."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cf12edc6459d4c6e98b9ebf0","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Draft: AI Agent Benchmarking = TDD for AI\n\n**𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.**\n\nWrite the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass.\n\nSame principle applies to AI agents — but almost nobody does it.\n\nMost teams start with the model. They iterate on prompts, chain-of-thought, RAG pipelines. Then they wonder why the agent drifts. Why it works today and breaks tomorrow.\n\nThe fix: **benchmark first.**\n\nDefine the verifiable outcome BEFORE you write a single line of agent logic.\n\nWhat's the task? What does \"done\" look like? How do you measure it?\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Your agent optimizes toward it. Every iteration moves the needle.\n\nThis is how you build self-evolving agents — not by hoping they figure it out, but by giving them a clear target and letting them chase it.\n\nTDD gave us reliable software. Benchmark-first gives us reliable AI.\n\nAre you building your agent around a benchmark — or just hoping it works?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #MachineLearning\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/draft-benchmark-tdd.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# Draft: AI Agent Benchmarking = TDD for AI\\n\\n**𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.**\\n\\nWrite the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass.\\n\\nSame principle applies to AI agents — but almost nobody does it.\\n\\nMost teams start with the model. They iterate on prompts, chain-of-thought, RAG pipelines. Then they wonder why the agent drifts. Why it works today and breaks tomorrow.\\n\\nThe fix: **benchmark first.**\\n\\nDefine the verifiable outcome BEFORE you write a single line of agent logic.\\n\\nWhat's the task? What does \\\"done\\\" look like? How do you measure it?\\n\\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Your agent optimizes toward it. Every iteration moves the needle.\\n\\nThis is how you build self-evolving agents — not by hoping they figure it out, but by giving them a clear target and letting them chase it.\\n\\nTDD gave us reliable software. Benchmark-first gives us reliable AI.\\n\\nAre you building your agent around a benchmark — or just hoping it works?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #MachineLearning\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/draft-benchmark-tdd.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783356364007,"responseId":"zdtLaomvDuro3PQPjpGxsAg"}}
