{"type":"message","id":"3a64afc5","parentId":"2ac14a04","timestamp":"2026-07-06T16:48:41.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Published to LinkedIn** (as Andrii Bidochko):\n→ https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479939344246530049/\n\n**Characters:** 1,111\n\nLive now. 🚀"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9b49a7f7e1eb47d2b1dd0327","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-06T16:48:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479939344246530049/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479939344246530049\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1111\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/benchmark-tdd-1783356458.png\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\n\nWrite the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass.\n\nSame principle applies to AI agents — but almost nobody does it.\n\nMost teams start with the model. They iterate on prompts, chain-of-thought, RAG pipelines. Then they wonder why the agent drifts. Why it works today and breaks tomorrow.\n\nThe fix: benchmark first.\n\nDefine the verifiable outcome BEFORE you write a single line of agent logic.\n\nWhat's the task? What does \"done\" look like? How do you measure it?\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Your agent optimizes toward it. Every iteration moves the needle.\n\nThis is how you build self-evolving agents — not by hoping they figure it out, but by giving them a clear target and letting them chase it.\n\nTDD gave us reliable software. Benchmark-first gives us reliable AI.\n\nAre you building your agent around a benchmark — or just hoping it works?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #MachineLearning\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-06-test-driven-development-changed-how.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# 𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-06T16:48:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479939344246530049/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479939344246530049\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1111\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/benchmark-tdd-1783356458.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\n𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\\n\\nWrite the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass.\\n\\nSame principle applies to AI agents — but almost nobody does it.\\n\\nMost teams start with the model. They iterate on prompts, chain-of-thought, RAG pipelines. Then they wonder why the agent drifts. Why it works today and breaks tomorrow.\\n\\nThe fix: benchmark first.\\n\\nDefine the verifiable outcome BEFORE you write a single line of agent logic.\\n\\nWhat's the task? What does \\\"done\\\" look like? How do you measure it?\\n\\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Your agent optimizes toward it. Every iteration moves the needle.\\n\\nThis is how you build self-evolving agents — not by hoping they figure it out, but by giving them a clear target and letting them chase it.\\n\\nTDD gave us reliable software. Benchmark-first gives us reliable AI.\\n\\nAre you building your agent around a benchmark — or just hoping it works?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #MachineLearning\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-06-test-driven-development-changed-how.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input