{"type":"message","id":"6be201b5","parentId":"bc6fe847","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:43:56.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4a88d329e63946fc80efec4d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-06-test-driven-development-changed-how.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-06-test-driven-development-changed-how.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b467172d586540eba3a0d365","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md","limit":50},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md\", \"limit\": 50}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783377827145,"responseId":"pS9MatSYGr-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c6111bf","parentId":"6be201b5","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:43:57.004Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4a88d329e63946fc80efec4d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-06T16:48:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479939344246530049/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479939344246530049\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1111\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/benchmark-tdd-1783356458.png\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗧𝗲𝘀𝘁-𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗲 𝘄𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲.\n\nWrite the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass.\n\nSame principle applies to AI agents — but almost nobody does it.\n\nMost teams start with the model. They iterate on prompts, chain-of-thought, RAG pipelines. Then they wonder why the agent drifts. Why it works today and breaks tomorrow.\n\nThe fix: benchmark first.\n\nDefine the verifiable outcome BEFORE you write a single line of agent logic.\n\nWhat's the task? What does \"done\" look like? How do you measure it?\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Your agent optimizes toward it. Every iteration moves the needle.\n\nThis is how you build self-evolving agents — not by hoping they figure it out, but by giving them a clear target and letting them chase it.\n\nTDD gave us reliable software. Benchmark-first gives us reliable AI.\n\nAre you building your agent around a benchmark — or just hoping it works?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #MachineLearning\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783377837002}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2397ce4","parentId":"9c6111bf","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:43:57.010Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b467172d586540eba3a0d365","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n[91 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783377837008}}
