{"type":"message","id":"89e0a095","parentId":"47e53531","timestamp":"2026-07-07T07:15:18.060Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a43dc2ea3cd54198b2e703e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. 𝗜𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗿𝗼𝘄. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nSound familiar?\n\nThis is the drift problem. Most agents have no anchor. They optimize for whatever feels right in the moment — but there's no fixed target.\n\nThe fix: **benchmark + reward function.**\n\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\n\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\n\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\n\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\n\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\n\n**Characters:** ~900\n\n---\n\n## Trend Proposals — 2026-07-03\n\n### Claude Fable 5 outage exposed a fatal gap: only 1 in 10 enterprises can auto-catch failing AI\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n\n[61 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783408518058}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ab67493","parentId":"89e0a095","timestamp":"2026-07-07T07:15:22.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fccd22e2971a4311be62a9dd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md","limit":60,"offset":80},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md\", \"limit\": 60, \"offset\": 80}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783408518083,"responseId":"iKdMau-hFMuIkuwPo_uciQE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d72351d8","parentId":"0ab67493","timestamp":"2026-07-07T07:15:22.679Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fccd22e2971a4311be62a9dd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\" — You built an AI agent. It went down. Did you even notice? Most teams have no fallback detection. That's the real risk.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\n**Persona:** CTO at 200+ person company — running production AI, can't afford silent failures\n**Status:** ✍️ Writing now\n\n---\n\n### Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 — by ditching general-purpose models\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The mistake most people will make\" — Most teams throw GPT-4 at everything. The winners are building specialized stacks that skip the bloat.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n**Persona:** CTO at IT consultancy — needs to deliver client projects faster with reusable components\n**Scheduled:** July 7, 2026 (Monday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### DeepSeek open-sourced DSpark — 85% faster LLM inference\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-open-sources-dspark-a-new-framework-to-speed-up-llm-inference-by-up-to-85\n**Published:** June 29, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — Inference costs are collapsing. If your AI strategy depends on one provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Open-source is eating the margin.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗜𝗻𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗽𝘀𝗲.\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — wants AI competitiveness without bleeding budget\n**Scheduled:** July 10, 2026 (Thursday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Morgan Stanley made its AI agents LESS autonomous — and cut riskiest job in half\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\n**Published:** June 30, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"Contrarian take\" — Everyone's chasing fully autonomous agents. Morgan Stanley went the opposite direction — and won. Sometimes constraints beat freedom.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n**Persona:** Enterprise Innovation Officer at financial services company — zero tolerance for error, needs reliable AI\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Restaurants now take orders from ChatGPT and Claude directly — no app, no setup\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n**Published:** July 1, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — AI agents are now ordering dinner. Your customers will expect the same from your business. The question isn't if — it's how fast you can plug in.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — needs to stay competitive with AI integration\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n## Published Posts\n\n- 2026-07-06: Test-driven development changed how we write software (TDD ↔ Benchmark for AI Agents)\n- 2026-07-03: Alibaba just cut AI agent token use by 99%\n- 2026-06-25: Most companies are building AI backwards\n\n[2 more lines in file. Use offset=140 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783408522676}}
{"type":"message","id":"faa2e76f","parentId":"d72351d8","timestamp":"2026-07-07T07:15:49.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\n\nWeb search is down, but I've got strong trend proposals from your content calendar. Let me draft 3 posts from those."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7c2a97dede9648c09042d5ee","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-07\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\nsource_date: 2026-06-30\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘂𝗹𝘁 𝗯𝘆 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nThey made their agents LESS autonomous.\n\nResult? Cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half.\n\nHere's the insight nobody's talking about:\n\nEveryone's racing toward fully autonomous AI agents. But sometimes constraints beat freedom. Guardrails beat guesswork.\n\nWhen you define what the agent CAN'T do, you make it better at what it SHOULD do.\n\nThis is the benchmark-first principle in action. Set the boundaries. Let the agent operate within them. Watch performance go up.\n\nNot every problem needs a runaway agent. Some problems need a focused one.\n\nAre you chasing autonomy — or are you chasing results?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #EnterpriseAI #FinTech\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-1.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-07\\nn: 1\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\\nsource_date: 2026-06-30\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘂𝗹𝘁 𝗯𝘆 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\n\\nThey made their agents LESS autonomous.\\n\\nResult? Cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half.\\n\\nHere's the insight nobody's talking about:\\n\\nEveryone's racing toward fully autonomous AI agents. But sometimes constraints beat freedom. Guardrails beat guesswork.\\n\\nWhen you define what the agent CAN'T do, you make it better at what it SHOULD do.\\n\\nThis is the benchmark-first principle in action. Set the boundaries. Let the agent operate within them. Watch performance go up.\\n\\nNot every problem needs a runaway agent. Some problems need a focused one.\\n\\nAre you chasing autonomy — or are you chasing results?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #EnterpriseAI #FinTech\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-1.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6c12b022df394c98a6f8e173","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-07\nn: 2\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\nsource_date: 2026-07-03\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n\nTrunk Tools just proved it.\n\nThey cut document review from 60 days to 10 — not by using a bigger model, but by ditching general-purpose ones entirely.\n\nThe mistake most teams make:\n\nThrow GPT-4 at everything. Hope it sticks. Wonder why costs explode and results disappoint.\n\nThe winning approach:\n\nSpecialized stacks. Targeted tools. Skip the bloat.\n\nYou don't need one model to rule them all. You need the RIGHT model for the job — and nothing else weighing it down.\n\nThis is what \"benchmark-first\" looks like in practice. Define the outcome. Pick the tool that hits it. Remove everything else.\n\nWhat's your AI stack — a swiss army knife or a precision tool?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #EnterpriseAI #DocumentProcessing\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-2.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-07\\nn: 2\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\\nsource_date: 2026-07-03\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\\n\\nTrunk Tools just proved it.\\n\\nThey cut document review from 60 days to 10 — not by using a bigger model, but by ditching general-purpose ones entirely.\\n\\nThe mistake most teams make:\\n\\nThrow GPT-4 at everything. Hope it sticks. Wonder why costs explode and results disappoint.\\n\\nThe winning approach:\\n\\nSpecialized stacks. Targeted tools. Skip the bloat.\\n\\nYou don't need one model to rule them all. You need the RIGHT model for the job — and nothing else weighing it down.\\n\\nThis is what \\\"benchmark-first\\\" looks like in practice. Define the outcome. Pick the tool that hits it. Remove everything else.\\n\\nWhat's your AI stack — a swiss army knife or a precision tool?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #EnterpriseAI #DocumentProcessing\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-2.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2465bf69458c4465a3cc220d","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 2026-07-07\nn: 3\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\nsource_date: 2026-07-01\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n\nRestaurants can now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude — no app, no setup, just AI-to-business transactions happening in real time.\n\nHere's what this actually means:\n\nAI agents are now CUSTOMERS.\n\nThey're not just building your product. They're buying from it. Ordering from it. Interacting with it.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. The question isn't if your business can plug into this — it's how fast.\n\nBecause the companies that figure out AI-as-customer first will have a moat everyone else is scrambling to catch up to.\n\nThe interface is shifting. The question is whether you're ready for it.\n\nIs your business ready to serve AI agents — or are you still optimizing for 2019?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Ecommerce #BusinessStrategy #CustomerExperience\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-3.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"---\\ndate: 2026-07-07\\nn: 3\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\\nsource_date: 2026-07-01\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\\n\\nRestaurants can now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude — no app, no setup, just AI-to-business transactions happening in real time.\\n\\nHere's what this actually means:\\n\\nAI agents are now CUSTOMERS.\\n\\nThey're not just building your product. They're buying from it. Ordering from it. Interacting with it.\\n\\nYour customers will expect the same. The question isn't if your business can plug into this — it's how fast.\\n\\nBecause the companies that figure out AI-as-customer first will have a moat everyone else is scrambling to catch up to.\\n\\nThe interface is shifting. The question is whether you're ready for it.\\n\\nIs your business ready to serve AI agents — or are you still optimizing for 2019?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Ecommerce #BusinessStrategy #CustomerExperience\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-07-draft-3.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783408522696,"responseId":"jadMateLDNTqjMoPs8Td6Qc"}}
