{"type":"message","id":"94d18022","parentId":"105b01fa","timestamp":"2026-07-07T07:16:35.783Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f138b0b411a34680bf6c5727","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘂𝗹𝘁 𝗯𝘆 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nThey made their agents LESS autonomous.\n\nResult? Cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half.\n\nHere's the insight nobody's talking about:\n\nEveryone's racing toward fully autonomous AI agents. But sometimes constraints beat freedom. Guardrails beat guesswork.\n\nWhen you define what the agent CAN'T do, you make it better at what it SHOULD do.\n\nThis is the benchmark-first principle in action. Set the boundaries. Let the agent operate within them. Watch performance go up.\n\nNot every problem needs a runaway agent. Some problems need a focused one.\n\nAre you chasing autonomy — or are you chasing results?\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Morgan Stanley cut its riskiest job in half (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-07-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-07-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-07-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]},"target":"264468965"},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘂𝗹𝘁 𝗯𝘆 𝗱𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲'𝘀 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\n\\nThey made their agents LESS autonomous.\\n\\nResult? Cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half.\\n\\nHere's the insight nobody's talking about:\\n\\nEveryone's racing toward fully autonomous AI agents. But sometimes constraints beat freedom. Guardrails beat guesswork.\\n\\nWhen you define what the agent CAN'T do, you make it better at what it SHOULD do.\\n\\nThis is the benchmark-first principle in action. Set the boundaries. Let the agent operate within them. Watch performance go up.\\n\\nNot every problem needs a runaway agent. Some problems need a focused one.\\n\\nAre you chasing autonomy — or are you chasing results?\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Morgan Stanley cut its riskiest job in half (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-07-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-07-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-07-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}, \"target\": \"264468965\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6b75251272ad42589694cf77","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n\nTrunk Tools just proved it.\n\nThey cut document review from 60 days to 10 — not by using a bigger model, but by ditching general-purpose ones entirely.\n\nThe mistake most teams make:\n\nThrow GPT-4 at everything. Hope it sticks. Wonder why costs explode and results disappoint.\n\nThe winning approach:\n\nSpecialized stacks. Targeted tools. Skip the bloat.\n\nYou don't need one model to rule them all. You need the RIGHT model for the job — and nothing else weighing it down.\n\nThis is what \"benchmark-first\" looks like in practice. Define the outcome. Pick the tool that hits it. Remove everything else.\n\nWhat's your AI stack — a swiss army knife or a precision tool?\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-07-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-07-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-07-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]},"target":"264468965"},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\\n\\nTrunk Tools just proved it.\\n\\nThey cut document review from 60 days to 10 — not by using a bigger model, but by ditching general-purpose ones entirely.\\n\\nThe mistake most teams make:\\n\\nThrow GPT-4 at everything. Hope it sticks. Wonder why costs explode and results disappoint.\\n\\nThe winning approach:\\n\\nSpecialized stacks. Targeted tools. Skip the bloat.\\n\\nYou don't need one model to rule them all. You need the RIGHT model for the job — and nothing else weighing it down.\\n\\nThis is what \\\"benchmark-first\\\" looks like in practice. Define the outcome. Pick the tool that hits it. Remove everything else.\\n\\nWhat's your AI stack — a swiss army knife or a precision tool?\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-07-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-07-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-07-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}, \"target\": \"264468965\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8202f117e68044dd9fe9acfb","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n\nRestaurants can now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude — no app, no setup, just AI-to-business transactions happening in real time.\n\nHere's what this actually means:\n\nAI agents are now CUSTOMERS.\n\nThey're not just building your product. They're buying from it. Ordering from it. Interacting with it.\n\nYour customers will expect the same. The question isn't if your business can plug into this — it's how fast.\n\nBecause the companies that figure out AI-as-customer first will have a moat everyone else is scrambling to catch up to.\n\nThe interface is shifting. The question is whether you're ready for it.\n\nIs your business ready to serve AI agents — or are you still optimizing for 2019?\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Restaurants accept orders from ChatGPT and Claude (https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-07-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-07-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-07-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]},"target":"264468965"},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\\n\\nRestaurants can now take orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude — no app, no setup, just AI-to-business transactions happening in real time.\\n\\nHere's what this actually means:\\n\\nAI agents are now CUSTOMERS.\\n\\nThey're not just building your product. They're buying from it. Ordering from it. Interacting with it.\\n\\nYour customers will expect the same. The question isn't if your business can plug into this — it's how fast.\\n\\nBecause the companies that figure out AI-as-customer first will have a moat everyone else is scrambling to catch up to.\\n\\nThe interface is shifting. The question is whether you're ready for it.\\n\\nIs your business ready to serve AI agents — or are you still optimizing for 2019?\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Restaurants accept orders from ChatGPT and Claude (https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-07-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-07-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-07-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}, \"target\": \"264468965\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783408573382,"responseId":"v6dMauvoGsfKwOYP6KGRmAY"}}
